# get all courses. 
# cannot do it in one request due to limit of 100 per. 
# use offset to get all.
# How do we know when were done?
# By manueal inspection, there are 13792 courses!


# loop, offessting by 100 from 0 to 13800 and append. this should get all!
all_courses1 = pd.DataFrame()
i = 0
#curr_df = pd.json_normalize(requests.get(f"https://planetterp.com/api/v1/courses").json()) # default offset = 0, limit = 100. 
while i < 13800:

    curr_df =  pd.json_normalize(requests.get(f"https://planetterp.com/api/v1/courses?offset={i}").json())
    all_courses1 = pd.concat([all_courses1, curr_df], ignore_index=True)
    i = i + 100

# Add a column for the gpa of the course. Weights taken from UMD website
all_grades["gpa"] = ((all_grades["A+"] + all_grades["A"]) * 4.0 + 
                     all_grades["A-"] * 3.7 +
                     all_grades["B+"] * 3.3 + 
                     all_grades["B"] * 3.0 + 
                     all_grades["B-"] * 2.7 + 
                     all_grades["C+"] *2.3 + 
                     all_grades["C"] * 2.0 + 
                     all_grades["C-"] * 1.7 + 
                     all_grades["D+"] * 1.3 + 
                     all_grades["D"] * 1.0 +
                     all_grades["D-"] * .7 + 
                     all_grades["F"] *0)/all_grades["total_students_graded"]

In [220]:
# Wow huge spike when school went online for covid! 
# and a large drop towards the trend in spring 2021 and fall 2022. 
# Question: What factors caused this inflation?
# The following come to mind:
# (i) UMD allowed taking a class pass/fail during these semesters. Students with lower grades likely opted for a pass rather than a below average grade. 
# (ii) Teachers were more lenient during this time due to the difficulty and stresses of the pandemic
# (iii) Students took advantage of online assessments (cheating).
In [221]:
# Lets try to see how much the pass fail option increased grades:
In [222]:
# For this analysis we will assume that if a student had a below average grade, they would opt to take the pass fail option. Above average, they likely kept their grade as is. 
# So we will replace a fraction of the other grades with the 3rd quartile gpa. To find the number of others to change, we will examine the average number of others for that course in previous semesters. 
# What should we use as an average grade for that semester? We will use the previous semester average
# pass fail option Spring 2021 (202101) for up to 7 creds. 
# pass fail option for ALL creds, Opt Out for spring 2020 202001. 
# no pass fail option fall 2021 (202108)

def abline(slope, intercept, ax, xlim):
    """Plot a line from slope and intercept"""
    axes = ax
    x_vals = np.array(xlim)
    
    y_vals = intercept + slope * x_vals
    ax.set(xlim=(2012, 2022.5))
    plt.plot(x_vals, y_vals, '--')

def abline(slope, intercept, ax, xlim):
    """Plot a line from slope and intercept"""
    axes = ax
    x_vals = np.array(xlim)
    
    y_vals = intercept + slope * x_vals
    ax.set(xlim=(2012, 2022.5))
    plt.plot(x_vals, y_vals, '--')
